<p>Para configurar a VPN da UFSC no Fedora, os pacotes a seguir devem ser instalados:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo dnf install strongswan*
sudo dnf install NetworkManager-strongswan NetworkManager-strongswan-gnome
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>O resto segue o mesmo to tutorial da UFSC. Adicionar a conexão IPsec/IKEv2 (strongswan).</p>

<p>Link para o tutorial ufsc <a href="https://servicosti.sistemas.ufsc.br/publico/detalhes.xhtml?servico=112">aqui</a></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="infrastructure" /><category term="vpn" /><category term="ufsc" /><category term="fedora" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[configuração vpn ufsc no fedora]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">aucc python implementation</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/blog/2023/aucc/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="aucc python implementation" /><published>2023-07-28T00:00:00-03:00</published><updated>2023-07-28T00:00:00-03:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/blog/2023/aucc</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/blog/2023/aucc/"><![CDATA[<style>body {text-align: justify}</style>

<p>Implementation for the Area Under the (ROC) Curve for Clustering (AUCC) is now available in Python.</p>

<p>Check it out <a href="https://github.com/pajaskowiak/aucc">here</a>.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="code" /><category term="clustering" /><category term="aucc" /><category term="validation" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[aucc python implementation]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">dbcv</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/blog/2023/dbcv/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="dbcv" /><published>2023-05-03T00:00:00-03:00</published><updated>2023-05-03T00:00:00-03:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/blog/2023/dbcv</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/blog/2023/dbcv/"><![CDATA[<style>body {text-align: justify}</style>

<p>In order to validate density-based clustering results, relative CVIs, such as Silhouette and Dunn cannot be directly applied. Simply put, such indices are based on distances between objects, not taking density information into account. Density-Based Clustering Validation (DBCV) is a relative validity criterion that can be applied in such a scenario. DBCV can be employed to select the best configuration of parameters for DBSCAN, for instance. The measure is described <a href="https://epubs.siam.org/doi/pdf/10.1137/1.9781611973440.96">here</a>.</p>

<p>If you want to use the measure, Matlab source code for DBCV provided <a href="https://github.com/pajaskowiak/dbcv">here</a>.</p>

<p>The synthetic data sets used in the paper (shown below), are also available in the github repository.</p>

